{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17645651","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17645651"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T20:19:26+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T20:19:26+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18124"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18124","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18124"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.25,0.1,0.6,0.05,0]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10838"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"73589"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10838","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10838"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18124"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"59059"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"5325"},{"type":"tags","id":"7399"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"25220"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25223"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"73589","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/73589"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following structures runs superior to the median nerve and brachial artery in the arm?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Brachialis muscle","Radial nerve","Biceps brachii muscle","Ulnar nerve","Triceps brachii muscle"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Ebiceps brachii muscle\u003C/strong\u003E is located anteriorly in the arm and runs superior to the median nerve and brachial artery. This muscle is a key landmark in the arm, and its tendon can be palpated in the antecubital fossa. Understanding this relationship is important in clinical settings, such as when assessing for potential nerve or vascular injury following trauma.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eulnar nerve\u003C/strong\u003E runs medially in the arm and is not positioned superior to the median nerve and brachial artery. It is more commonly associated with the medial epicondyle of the humerus.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eradial nerve\u003C/strong\u003E is located posteriorly in the arm and travels in the radial groove of the humerus. It is not positioned superior to the median nerve and brachial artery.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Ebrachialis muscle\u003C/strong\u003E lies deep to the biceps brachii and is not superior to the median nerve and brachial artery. It is primarily involved in elbow flexion.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Etriceps brachii muscle\u003C/strong\u003E is located posteriorly in the arm and is not positioned superior to the median nerve and brachial artery. It is responsible for elbow extension.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The median nerve and brachial artery are key structures in the arm, with specific anatomical relationships.","Understanding the anatomical positioning of nerves and arteries is crucial for clinical procedures such as venipuncture and surgery."],"references":["West, S. G. (2019). Anatomy and physiology of the musculoskeletal system. Rheumatology Secrets E-Book: Rheumatology Secrets E-Book, 17","Miniato MA, Anand P, Varacallo M. Anatomy, Shoulder and Upper Limb, Shoulder. 2023 Jul 24. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 30725618","Hutson, M., \u0026 Ward, A. (Eds.). (2015). Oxford textbook of musculoskeletal medicine. Oxford University Press","McCausland C, Sawyer E, Eovaldi BJ, Varacallo M. Anatomy, Shoulder and Upper Limb, Shoulder Muscles. 2023 Aug 8. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 30521257","Paulsen, F., \u0026 Waschke, J. (Eds.). (2023). Sobotta Atlas of Anatomy, Vol. 1, English/Latin: General Anatomy and Musculoskeletal System (Vol. 1). Elsevier Health Sciences"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"59059"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18124"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"59059","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/59059"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-24T00:22:17+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-13T00:38:58+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10838"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"73589"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading